      <title>“Latent Spacecraft: Brains, GANs, Finnegans” is out today. (DOI 10.1162/ANTI.5KP...</title>
      <link>https://www.instagram.com/p/DUVJuoADekh/</link>
      <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/628028202_18373233793095126_7276593658663031537_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_p360x360_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=108&amp;ig_cache_key=MzgyNTAwMjkyMDg2NjA4NDY1NQ%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjcyMHg5MDAuc2RyLkMzIn0%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=6HTxNXKaKHAQ7kNvwG-yooS&amp;_nc_oc=AdqXcLNs88UglmhmVbXyoJHCBqomEbBTxbN1sPrAejhMCWabKJPXIVBd-T5IT9T4fZ4&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=C3WV2qxIuE6Yt1tuomrbxg&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfyvwkGjSG8fw4JK_F-7yyv_brMTFEfR5fAsn5LZyx7fTg&amp;oe=69C983AF" alt="Instagram billede fra @metahaven" /></p><p><strong>@metahaven</strong></p><p>“Latent Spacecraft: Brains, GANs, Finnegans” is out today. (DOI 10.1162/ANTI.5KPI). This project argues that latent space—the learned, multidimensional, representational substrate of neural networks—is not only a mathematical construct but, read through literature, a structure akin to architectural interiority that renders the abstract physically legible. We stage three case studies to trace deep homologies between biological and synthetic language: (1) speech-producing brains alongside speech-generating GANs, which learn by informative imitation and exhibit imagitation, which exceeds mere replication; (2) James Joyce’s Finnegans Wake as a cartography of latent space, where nonce words and associative syntax model pre-narrative interiority; and (3) FinneGANs, a GAN trained on Finnegans Wake audio, whose outputs probe the limits of comprehensibility and pre-speech form. Across these isomorphs, we contend that language is a final, linearizing layer over a generative, precategorial interior. Architecture serves as a navigable armature of the interior, where the symbolic layer is often physical, all the way to the deepest layers. 🌑 Find the article and the models at latentspacecraft.antikythera.org 🌑 Nina Beguš, Metahaven, Gašper Beguš with Metahaven and Riccardo Petrini 🌑 Slides: 1. Title / 2. FinneGAN model / 3. Scroll / 4. The Thick Cursor / 5. fiwGAN model</p>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/628028202_18373233793095126_7276593658663031537_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_p360x360_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=108&amp;ig_cache_key=MzgyNTAwMjkyMDg2NjA4NDY1NQ%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjcyMHg5MDAuc2RyLkMzIn0%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=6HTxNXKaKHAQ7kNvwG-yooS&amp;_nc_oc=AdqXcLNs88UglmhmVbXyoJHCBqomEbBTxbN1sPrAejhMCWabKJPXIVBd-T5IT9T4fZ4&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=C3WV2qxIuE6Yt1tuomrbxg&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfyvwkGjSG8fw4JK_F-7yyv_brMTFEfR5fAsn5LZyx7fTg&amp;oe=69C983AF" alt="Instagram billede fra @metahaven" /></p><p><strong>@metahaven</strong></p><p>“Latent Spacecraft: Brains, GANs, Finnegans” is out today. (DOI 10.1162/ANTI.5KPI). This project argues that latent space—the learned, multidimensional, representational substrate of neural networks—is not only a mathematical construct but, read through literature, a structure akin to architectural interiority that renders the abstract physically legible. We stage three case studies to trace deep homologies between biological and synthetic language: (1) speech-producing brains alongside speech-generating GANs, which learn by informative imitation and exhibit imagitation, which exceeds mere replication; (2) James Joyce’s Finnegans Wake as a cartography of latent space, where nonce words and associative syntax model pre-narrative interiority; and (3) FinneGANs, a GAN trained on Finnegans Wake audio, whose outputs probe the limits of comprehensibility and pre-speech form. Across these isomorphs, we contend that language is a final, linearizing layer over a generative, precategorial interior. Architecture serves as a navigable armature of the interior, where the symbolic layer is often physical, all the way to the deepest layers. 🌑 Find the article and the models at latentspacecraft.antikythera.org 🌑 Nina Beguš, Metahaven, Gašper Beguš with Metahaven and Riccardo Petrini 🌑 Slides: 1. Title / 2. FinneGAN model / 3. Scroll / 4. The Thick Cursor / 5. fiwGAN model</p>]]></content:encoded>
